    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2c986-102">使用して、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute>を呼び出すと、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer.Serialize%2A>または<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer.Deserialize%2A>のメソッド、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer>クラス。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-102">Use the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute> when you call the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer.Serialize%2A> or <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer.Deserialize%2A> method of the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer> class.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2c986-103">適用するときに、 <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute>、指定、<xref:System.Type>の派生クラス。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-103">When applying the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute>, specify the <xref:System.Type> of the derived class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2c986-104">ときに、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer>基本と、派生クラスの両方を含むオブジェクトをシリアル化します。 両方のオブジェクトの種類を認識できますしします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-104">When the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSerializer> serializes objects that include both the base and the derived class, it can then recognize both object types.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2c986-105">使用することができます、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute>派生クラスを Web サービス記述言語 (WSDL) で記述されたサービスの説明のドキュメントに含める。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-105">You can use the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute> to include derived classes in service description documents that are written in the Web Services Description Language (WSDL).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2c986-106">メソッドから返された場合など、 <xref:System.Object>、適用、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute>メソッドに返される実際の型を指定します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-106">For example, if a method returns an <xref:System.Object>, apply the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute> to the method and specify the actual types to return.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2c986-107">WSDL の詳細については、「Web サービス記述言語 (WSDL) 1.1」www.w3.org でを参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-107">For more information on the WSDL, see "Web Services Description Language (WSDL) 1.1" at www.w3.org.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="2c986-108">次の例では、3 番目から継承する 2 つ、3 つのクラスを示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-108">The following example shows three classes, two of which inherit from the third.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2c986-109">例では、適用、<xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute>を派生クラスの 1 つのインスタンスを返すメソッドにします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2c986-109">The example applies the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute> to a method that returns an instance of one of the derived classes.</span></span>  
  
  
  
